In a conversation with President Volodymyr Zelenskyy of Ukraine, President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. expressed the United States' commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity. He strongly condemned Russian President Putin's decision to recognize the "independence" of the DNR and LNR regions of Ukraine. President Biden informed President Zelenskyy about the US plan to issue sanctions in response to Russia's actions. He also emphasized that the United States would respond quickly and firmly, in coordination with its allies and partners, to any further Russian aggression against Ukraine.